  <owl:Ontology rdf:about="https://formenteraops.com/ontology/welldrive">
    <rdfs:comment>WellDrive well-file ontology for doc-intel knowledge-graph typing. Seeded from corpus entry_types and analyst classes; open knowledge-layer artifact (plan KTD5/U2).</rdfs:comment>
  </owl:Ontology>
  <owl:Class rdf:about="#Well"><rdfs:comment>A wellbore: the central entity documents attach to.</rdfs:comment></owl:Class>
  <owl:Class rdf:about="#Operator"><rdfs:comment>Company operating a well (e.g. Devon, EnCana, Formentera Operations).</rdfs:comment></owl:Class>
  <owl:Class rdf:about="#ServiceVendor"><rdfs:comment>Service company performing work (frac, cementing, wireline, directional).</rdfs:comment></owl:Class>
  <owl:Class rdf:about="#Formation"><rdfs:comment>Geologic formation a well penetrates or targets.</rdfs:comment></owl:Class>
  <owl:Class rdf:about="#County"><rdfs:comment>County/parish where a well is located.</rdfs:comment></owl:Class>
  <owl:Class rdf:about="#AssetTeam"><rdfs:comment>Formentera asset team owning the well (FP Griffin, Formentera South Texas, Westlake Resources).</rdfs:comment></owl:Class>
  <owl:Class rdf:about="#Event"><rdfs:comment>Dated operational occurrence: a test, frac job, workover, spud, completion.</rdfs:comment></owl:Class>
  <owl:Class rdf:about="#DocumentClass"><rdfs:comment>Class of well-file document, keyed by WellDrive entry_type metadata.</rdfs:comment></owl:Class>
